its and paradigm-changing discoveries, to her celebrity friendships, failed marriages, and scandalous affairs, and Prose delivers a colorful portrait of a defiantly uncompromising woman who maintained a powerful upper hand in a male-dominated world. Prose also explores the ways in which Guggenheim’s image was filtered through the lens of insidious antisemitism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArtxBiographyxCollectors and collectingxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aArtxCollectors and collectingzUnited StatesvBiography. 0aWomen art collectorsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aWomen art collectorszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Rich & Famous.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021652340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300216523423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300216523/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles